               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400914-name-119" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400914-name-119" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400914-name-119" type="surname" value="MAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400914-name-119" type="given" value="JOHN NISBETT"></interp>JOHN NISBETT MAN</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at Kennington. On the 4th of Sep<lb></lb>tember, about half-past eight o'clock, I was talking to a friend on Ludgate-hill—I felt some papers move which were in my pocket—I had my handkerchief in that pocket—I turned and saw the prisoner taking my handkerchief from my pocket—this is it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PHILLIPS</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Before the Magistrate, did you state that you saw him taking the handkerchief from you? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, I did.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did you not say, "I turned round and saw the prisoner with my handkerchief in his hand?" <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes; but I saw him take it from my pocket, and I told the Magistrate so—what I said was taken down and read to me—my handkerchief was partly in my pocket—my pocket is behind me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
